</small>\n|no2=699\n|name2=Aurorus\n|type1-2=Rock\n|type2-2=Ice}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=rock|type2=ice}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=698}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=698}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|698|Amaura}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* No other Pokémon has the same [[type]] [[List of Pokémon with unique type combinations|combination]] as Amaura and {{p|Aurorus|its evolution}}.\n* Amaura and its {{p|Aurorus|evolution}} were designed by [[Hitoshi Ariga]].<ref>[http://hitoshiariga.deviantart.com/art/Pocket-Monsters-XY-413536751 Pocket Monsters XY by HitoshiAriga on deviantART]</ref>\n\n===Origin===\nAmaura is based on a young {{wp|Sauropod|sauropod}} dinosaur. It bears a strong resemblance to \'\'{{wp|Amargasaurus}}\'\', which were speculated to have skin sail extensions on their vertebral spines. It also shares traits with various species of {{wp|Diplodocoidea}}. The color-changing sails upon its head are also based on {{wp|aurora}}s, most likely aurora borealis due to it being Ice-type.\n\n====Name origin====\nAmaura may be a contraction of \'\'Amargasaurus\'\' combined with \'\'aurora\'\'.\n\nAmarus may be a contraction of \'\'Amargasaurus\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Rock|type2=Ice\n|ja=アマルス \'\'Amarus\'\'|jameaning=Possibly a contraction of \'\'{{wp|Amargasaurus}}\'\'\n|fr=Amagara|frmeaning=From \'\'Amargasaurus\'\'\n|es=Amaura|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Amarino|demeaning=From \'\'Amargasaurus\'\', \'\'{{tt|Aquamarin|aquamarine}}\'\', and \'\'{{tt|Dinosaurier|dinosaur}}\'\'\n|it=Amaura|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=아마루스 \'\'Amaruseu\'\'|komeaning=Similar to Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=冰雪龍 \'\'Bīngxuělóng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|冰雪 \'\'bīngxuě\'\'|snow and ice}} and {{tt|恐龍 \'\'kǒnglóng\'\'|dinosaur}}\n|zh_yue=冰雪龍 \'\'Bīngsyutlùhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|冰雪 \'\'bīngsyut\'\'|snow and ice}} and {{tt|恐龍 \'\'húnglùhng\'\'|dinosaur}}\n|hi=अमौरा \'\'Amaura\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Амаура \'\'Amaura\'\'|rumeaning=Transliteration of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Rock|type2=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Rock|prevnum=697|prev=Tyrantrum|nextnum=699|next=Aurorus}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Fossil Pokémon]]\n[[Category:Pokémon that evolve based on time]]\n[[Category:Pokémon that evolve only at night]]\n\n[[de:Amarino]]\n[[es:Amaura]]\n[[fr:Amagara]]\n[[it:Amaura]]\n[[ja:アマルス]]\n[[zh:冰雪龙]]'}